(firstQuint)Performance Characteristics and Safety Assessment of a Non-invasive Glucose Monitoring Device.

 Subjects will collect spectral raman data on device every 15 minutes for 10 hours a day for five days.

 The five days will be distributes with in a timeframe of ten days.

 A Flash Glucose Monitor will be used as a comparator.

 In addition to this, four daily capillary Blood Glucose readings will be collected.

